$__information['sshconfig_updateform_update_pre'] = "Snapshots zijn de exacte kopie van de database en de bestanden van uw aanvraag op een bepaald tijdstip. U kunt uw aanvraag tot een bepaald snapshot door te klikken op de [b] te herstellen [/ b]-knop."; // It is recommended that you completely disable password based access to this server, and instead use the  <url:goback=1&a=list&c=sshauthorizedkey>ssh authorization key manager </url> to allow specific people to access without password. If this is hyperVM, and you are intending to sell VPSes to other people, you won't be able to completely disable ssh password access, since vps-owners will need to login the node to access their consoles. In any case, make sure you disable password based root access to this server. So as a rule of thumb, on kloxo, disable password access to everything, while on hyperVM, disable password access to root alone.
$__information['all_dns_list__pre'] = "Uw admin is niet ingeschakeld shell toegang voor jou. Open dan een support ticket als u SSH toegang."; // This is the list of every dns created by your VPS owners. <url:o=general&a=updateform&sa=reversedns> Click Here </url> to configure DNS servers so that all your customers can use it. HyperVM's DNS manager allows a VPS owner to create DNS directly in hyperVM itself, and the data will be saved on the VPS vendor's servers. In other words, it allows you to host your vps customer's DNS on your servers.
$__information['actionlog_list__pre'] = "Let op dat alle uw activiteit is aangemeld en elke poging om toegang te krijgen tot bestanden die niet behoren tot je zal leiden tot beëindiging van uw hosting account. Hiermee op verantwoorde wijze kunt u handelen."; // Action log records all the actions executed on a client or a vps. The important thing you should note is that the auxiliary id of the person logged in is properly recorded here. So you should never give out the main account to anyone, instead create <url:a=list&c=auxiliary> auxiliary identities </url>for each of your staff.
$__information['sshauthorizedkey_list__pre'] = "Dit is de toegang log voor je domein. U kunt downloaden door te klikken op de [b] downloaden [/ b] tab aan de rechterkant. Dit bestand bevat informatie over elke hit die is gemaakt naar uw website"; // Please note, the ~/.ssh/authorized_keys2 file has been deprecated as of openssh version 3, and so only the ~/.ssh/authorized_keys file is managed. These are the ssh keys from the machines which can login to this server without providing password. Make sure you keep this list trimmed.
$__information['updateform_forcedeletepserver_pre'] = "Al uw kinderen zullen erven automatisch uitschakelen van uw URL-parameters. Af te dwingen je uitschakelen URL op hen, gewoon uitschakelen hun &#39;kunt uitschakelen URL&#39; in de permissie-instellingen. Dit is de URL waarop een domeinnaam wordt doorgestuurd naar wanneer deze is uitgeschakeld."; // Force delete Server just removes the server from hyperVM's database. This is useful if the server has been completely removed is no longer accessible.
$__information['allowedip_addform__pre'] = "Wijzen slechts een dns template aan uw klant. Dit zou betekenen dat kloxo niet de dns sjabloon te selecteren vak laten zien, terwijl het toevoegen van een domein, waardoor het minder verwarrend is voor uw klant."; // Please note: This is only meant for blocking access to the control panel, and will not block access to the actual resource. You can add an ip of the form [b] 192.168.1.*[/b]  denote a range. That is, instead of providing a number, you can use [b] * [/b]  to represent the entire range. You can also add individual ips of the form 192.168.1.2. Please note that the dotted notation is necessary, and you have to provide all the 4 fields. If you want to allow everyone, remove all the allowed ips, or provide [b] *.*.*.* [/b]. Other IP notations are not supported at this point.
$__information['blockedip_addform__pre'] = "De forward-adressen zijn een lijst van e-mailadressen waarop de mail wordt doorgestuurd. Een kopie van de e-mail wordt opgeslagen om de werkelijke mailaccount ook. U kunt uitschakelen lokale opslag door <url:a=updateform&sa=configuration> hier te klikken </url> ."; //  Please note: This is only meant for blocking access to the control panel, and will not block access to the actual resource. This is the list of blocked ipaddresses. The ip notation is the same as that of allowed ip. You should add blocked ips only if the allowed ip list is empty. If allowed ip list is non-empty then, automatically all ips not listed are denied.
$__information['updateform_portconfig_pre'] = "Uw adres is geblokkeerd"; // This page is primarily meant to configure the ports of Kloxo/HyperVM. After making the changes here, you will need to restart Kloxo/HyperVM service once for the changes to take effect. Run this command [b] cd /usr/local/lxlabs/<%program%>/httpdocs ; lphp.exe ../bin/common/misc/defaultport.php [/b] and the ports will be reset to the default. You can then restart Kloxo/HyperVM. Leave the fields blank to revert to default ports. 
