$__information['updateform_ssl_kloxo_pre'] = "Zorg voor een correcte Set Your EMAILID"; // This will set the ssl certificate for <%program%> as this particular certificate. Make sure you restart <%program%> after you set it here.
$__information['updateform_ssl_authorized_keys_pre'] = "Kan geen verbinding met de server [% s]. Dit is waarschijnlijk te wijten aan onderliggende probleem met het netwerk. Zorg ervoor dat de server toegankelijk is via deze specifieke node door het uitvoeren van [b] telnet slave-id 7779 [/ b]"; // These are the SSH keys from the machines which are authorized to login to your account without supplying the password. They are kept as 1 per line. You can add the keys to the machines you want to have password-less access to this machine. You should also keep this file trimmed so as to reduce the chances of unwanted people logging in
$__information['updateform_ssl_hypervm_pre'] = "Herstarten van de backend. Probeer het opnieuw na 30 seconden."; // This will set the ssl certificate for <%program%> as this particular certificate. Make sure you restart <%program%> after you set it here.
$__information['updateform_selfbackupconfig_pre'] = "Quota overschreden voor [% s]"; //  This is primarily meant to configure the remote backup of the master database and nothing else. The database dump is taken everyday and is saved in a local folder in this machine. If an ftp account is configured here, the file will be uploaded to the machine. This is mainly useful in large cluster setup where the failure of master can have much larger impacts.
$__information['lxguard_updateform_update_pre'] = "Het publiek ipadres [% s] van deze server is niet gevonden in in de licentie repository. Neem contact op met Lxlabs verkopen of met uw dealer om een licentie voor deze server te maken."; //  Lxguard protects you against brute force attacks by monitoring the ssh and ftp log messages, and blocking ipaddresses that have too many failed attempts at logging into the server. Lxguard is default turned on, and will automatically block hosts, and cannot be turned off. You can configure Lxguard by specifying the [b] threshold of failed attempts [/b] or by adding certain ipaddresses to the whitelist. If an IP is found in the whitelist, it won't be blocked, even if it has crossed the threshold of failed attempts. To remove the warnings you get about Lxguard please click on the agreement checkbox below
$__information['updateform_generalsetting_pre'] = "Je hebt niet uitgeschakeld basis van een wachtwoord toegang tot root op deze server. Basis van een wachtwoord toegang tot root is niet nodig aangezien u kunt uw ssh erkende toetsen via HyperVM zelf. <url:k[class]=pserver&k[nname]=localhost&a=updateform&sa=update&o=sshconfig> Klik hier </url> om je SSH-server te configureren."; //  The 'HelpDesk Url' is a link to your Helpdesk, which will be used in place of the default help desk built into the software. Community Url is the link the client will see on his left page, and in normal cases can point to your forum.
$__information['custombutton_addform__pre'] = "De bron van de naam [% s] bestaat reeds."; //  In the url, you can use %nname%, which will be substituted with the name of the client. For Kloxo only, you can use %default_domain% for the default domain of the client.
$__information['updateform_download_config_pre'] = "Lxguard voor deze server is niet geconfigureerd. Gelieve <url:k[class]=pserver&k[nname]=localhost&a=show&o=lxguard> Klik hier om Lxguard configureren </url> want het is erg belangrijk dat je begrijpt wat het doet. Lxguard is essentieel voor de veiligheid van uw server, op hetzelfde moment, het kan je eigen ipadres blokkeren de toegang tot de server, die kan frustrerend zijn als je niet weet wat er gebeurt."; // Normally, when downloading files, the master creates a temporary session, and then redirects the browser directly to the slave. This is to save the bandwidth, since otherwise, the files are pointlessly have to go through the master. If you enable this, hyperVM will instead route the file via the master itself. This is useful if you have given private ips for slaves, and the slaves are not accessible from the outside world.
$__information['updateform_login_options_pre'] = "Directory die u heeft opgegeven bestaat reeds. Root gebruiker kan niet uitpakken archief in een bestaande map. Geef de naam van een directory die niet bestaat in het systeem."; //  Note: session timeout cannot be less than 100 and if less, will be automatically set to 100.
